    main
      section#more
        h2.hidden Information
        .indigo.container
          .image-container.information-paragraph.wow.fadeInUp
            img(src="/images/family.jpeg" alt="Picture of the Drs. Craig with their daughter Autumn and dog Wilson")
            
        .blue.container
          .content-container.information-paragraph.wow.fadeInUp
            p Dr. Anthony Craig works with his wife, Dr. Allison Craig, in Dixon, CA, at <a href="https://mapleleaf.dental" title="Link to our new office website">Maple Leaf Dental</a>. The Drs. Craig live in Vacaville with their daughter, Autumn, and their dog, Wilson.
            
        .green.container
          .content-container.information-paragraph.wow.fadeInUp
            p In addition to routine dental services such as <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dental_restoration" title="Wikipeida: Dental restorations">fillings</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crown_(dentistry)" title="Wikipedia: Dental crowns">crowns</a>, and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dentures" title="Wikipedia: Dentures"> dentures</a>, Dr. Craig has a thorough understanding of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CAD/CAM_dentistry" title="Wikipedia: CAD/CAM dentistry">CAD/CAM dentistry</a>, and can restore most <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dental_implant" title="Wikipedia: Dental implants">dental implants</a>.

        .yellow.container
          .content-container.information-paragraph.wow.fadeInUp
            p Dr. Craig grew up in Central California. In 2009, he graduated from <a href="http://www.puc.edu/academics/departments/chemistry/home" title="PUC Chemistry Department">Pacific Union College</a>, near Napa, California. After college, he matriculated to <a href="https://dentistry.llu.edu" title="Link to LLUSD">Loma Linda University School of Dentistry</a>, in Loma Linda, California, and graduated in 2013.

        .orange.container
          .content-container.information-paragraph.wow.fadeInUp
            p When he's not working, Dr. Craig enjoys mostly old things: <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Porsche_911_(964)" title="Link to Wikipedia article on the Porsche 964">air-cooled Porsche's</a>, <a href="https://www.l-camera-forum.com/leica-wiki.en/index.php/Walter_Mandler" title="Link to L Camera Forum page on Walter Mandler">vintage glass</a>, classic <a href="https://deskthority.net/wiki/Apple_Extended_Keyboard" title="Link to Deskthority page on the AEK">Apple</a>/<a href="https://imgur.com/a/RvxtF" title="Link to Imgur photo essay on NeXT's keyboards">NeXT</a> hardware, and <a href="https://community.hodinkee.com/members/toniwonkanobi" title="Link to my HODINKEE profile">mechanical watches</a> as well. He plays some <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LvhfpJ_6Hoo" title="Playing for the Michael Jackson concert">guitar</a>, and knows more about <a href="https://theoveranalyzed.net/tags/Star%20Wars" title="Dr. Craig's posts about Star Wars">Star Wars</a> than any dentist should.

        .red.container
          .content-container.information-paragraph.wow.fadeInUp
            p If coming to the dentist is something you dread, fear not&mdash;Dr. Craig is ready to help!

        .violet.container
          .content-container.information-paragraph.wow.fadeInUp
            p Taking care of the patient's dental issues is very important. But what is even <em>more</em> important is making that patient feel welcome, comfortable, and safe.

